fields.name: Omega New 2021 Speedmaster Moonwatch
fields.description: Inspired by the 4th generation Speedmaster style worn on the moon, The Speedmaster Moonwatch is one of Omega’s most iconic timepieces. Having been part of all six moon landings, this legendary watch captures the heart of brand’s pioneering spirit. Demonstrating the brand’s commitment to evolution, this new 2021 edition, offers even more reliability, precision and excellence with Master Chronometer certification.
fields.features: Inspired by the 4th generation Speedmaster style worn on the moon, Driven by the OMEGA Co-Axial Master Chronometer 3861 calibre movement

fields.name: Omega Seamaster Planet Ocean
fields.description: This model, with its scratch-resistant sapphire crystal, features a black ceramic dial with Arabic numerals and a date window at the 3 o’clock position. The black ceramic unidirectional bezel with OMEGA Liquidmetal™ diving scale is mounted on a 43.5 mm stainless steel case.

fields.description: A timeless collection since 1994, the OMEGA De Ville Prestige is now in its third generation. Continuing to represent classical design and refined elegance, the timepieces offer a range of patterns, finishes and colours to suit different lifestyles and personalities.

fields.name: Patek Philippe Aquanaut
fields.description: Patek Philippe is reasserting the contemporary casual chic spirit of the Aquanaut flyback chronograph with the first white gold version of this self-winding model, combined with an elegant midnight blue color for the dial and matching composite strap. The dial is enlivened by a black-gradient rim. Water-resistant to 120 m, the case is enhanced by polished and satin finishes. The 60-minute counter at 6 o'clock picks up the rounded octagonal shape of the bezel. The patented fold-over clasp is secured by four independent catches.
fields.features: Watch Markers Arabic Numerals, Water Resistant 120 Metres, Strap MaterialRubber, Recipient For Him, Movement Automatic

fields.name: Patek Philippe Calatrava
fields.description: The Ladies' Calatrava with its guilloched lacquered dial features a slightly larger diameter (35mm) and a self-winding movement replacing the previous manually wound caliber. Finely adorned with concentric waves, the dial plate is coated with several successive layers of transparent midnight blue lacquer creating a subtle depth effect. The bezel is lit up by 76 round-cut internally flawless Top Wesselton diamonds. This new model comes with a brushed calfskin strap featuring a satinated finish in a color matching that of the dial.
fields.features: Dial Colour Blue, Case Material 18ct White Gold, Diameter 35mm

fields.name: Patek Philippe Complication
fields.description: As the first stainless steel version of a cult model, the new Ref. 5935A-001 self-winding World Time flyback chronograph stands out with its sporty vintage looks. The carbon motif in the center of the opaline rose gilt dial reflects a modern, dynamic spirit.
fields.features: Movement Automatic, Case Material Stainless Steel, Diameter 41mm

fields.name: Patek Philippe Grand Complication
fields.description: A paragon of visual balance and legibility, the perpetual calendar model bearing Reference 5320 was designed in 2017 in a white gold case with a cream-lacquered dial. Its vintage style is reinterpreted in a new white gold version fitted with a gilded opaline rose gold dial.

fields.name: Rolex Air King
fields.description: A tribute to explorers of the skies, the Air-King celebrates the pioneers of aviation and invites wearers to take command of their own destiny. Rolex is presenting the new-generation Oyster Perpetual Air-King. The watch features a completely redesigned case with a crown guard and straight sides like the majority of Professional category models. The proportions of the bracelet have also been revisited, and notably the centre link has been broadened. In a first for the model, it is equipped with an Oysterlock safety clasp. The watch’s display has also been refreshed and is perfectly balanced thanks to the addition of a “0” before the “5” on the minutes scale. Each five-minute interval is, therefore, now marked by two digits.
fields.features: Oyster, 40 mm, Oystersteel, Approximately 70 hours, BRACELET, Oyster, flat three-piece links, DIAL, Black

fields.name: Rolex Cosmograph Daytona
fields.description: Launched in 1963, the Oyster Perpetual Cosmograph Daytona was designed to meet the needs of professional racing drivers. The Cosmograph Daytona is the benchmark for those with a passion for driving and speed. It is available in a variety of versions and materials, including with a dial made from metallic meteorite – a rare natural material from outer space – with black chronograph counters at 3, 6 and 9 o'clock.
fields.features: Oyster, 40 mm, Everose gold, Fixed, with engraved tachymetric scale, in 18 ct Everose gold, Waterproof to 100 metres / 330 feet
